<subSubSection pageNumber="681" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="681">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="681">Note:</emphasis>
Epling (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="681">J. Bot.</emphasis>
67: 4. 1929) noted material at LINN but did not designate a type. McClintock &amp; Epling (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="681">Univ. Calif. Publ. Bot.</emphasis>
20: 158. 1942) treated material in the Linnaean herbarium as &quot;the standard&quot; (not the same as a type) and Scora (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="681">Univ. Calif. Publ. Bot.</emphasis>
41: 31. 1967) suggested that this &quot;may be taken as the type&quot;. Wijnands appears to have been the first to make an unequivocal type designation.
</paragraph>
